article.description: Jonas Harper had a season-high 22 points as Boston University got past Holy Cross 70-60 on Monday night.
article.headline: Harper scores 22 to lift Boston U. past Holy Cross 70-60
article.linkText: Harper scores 22 to lift Boston U. past Holy Cross 70-60
article.story: WORCESTER, Mass. -- Jonas Harper had a season-high 22 points as Boston University got past Holy Cross 70-60 on Monday night. Harper made 8 of 10 shots, including 6 of 8 on 3-pointers. Max Mahoney had 11 points and 12 rebounds for Boston University (12-16, 5-10 Patriot League), which snapped its four-game losing streak. Tyler Scanlon added eight assists. Jehyve Floyd had 18 points, 12 rebounds and five blocks for the Crusaders (14-14, 5-10). Austin Butler added 17 points. The Terriers improve to 2-0 against the Crusaders for the season. Boston University defeated Holy Cross 68-54 on Jan. 30. Boston University takes on Loyola (Md.) at home on Saturday. Holy Cross faces Lehigh on the road on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
